description:
Job Descriptions:

Responsible for purchasing & operation activities from business contracts, sourcing, price negotiation, orders, shipment;

Collaborate with sales team and liaise with suppliers to drive on time shipment delivery;
Liaise and support post-contract management activities like handling deliveries discrepancies and monitoring supplier performance;
Handle full set of shipping I/E documents, liaise with supplier and forwarders for shipment schedule and arrangement;
Prepare regular reporting and conduct analysis to support business decisions;
Assist in other ad-hoc assignment as required.

Job Requirements:

Degree holder majoring in Purchasing, Supply Chain Management or other related subjects with at least 2 years related working experience, with background in purchasing field or manufacturing industry will be a plus;

Fluent in spoken and written English & Chinese (Cantonese and Mandarin);
Well versed with PC applications, i.e. MS Word, Excel, PowerPoint & Chinese Word Processing;
Patient, detailed-mind, willing to learn, able to work under pressure;
Well-organized with good interpersonal and communication skills;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Planning & Operation Executive.

Benefits:

5-day work (staggered working hours)
Double pay
Discretionary bonus
Group medical
OT pay
Statutory Annual Leave with extra 7 days Company Annual Leave
Bank Holiday
Other Special Leave i.e. Marriage Leave, etc.

We offer competitive remuneration and benefits, holidays, stable working environment to the right candidates. Interested parties please click "Apply Now" and send your full resume with expected salary in MS Word Format to us (Please quote Position Name & Reference No.)

*All personal data collected will be kept strictly confidential and used for recruitment-related purpose only.

Form 5 or above;
3-5 years working experience in garment accessories / packaging products field;
Trims orders follow up / co-ordination with client and factory
Well organized and good team player;
Good communication & interpersonal skills;
Able to communicate English and Mandarin
Less experience candidates will also considered as Assistant Merchandiser

 Interested parties, please send your resume with expected salary by clicking the below "apply now" button. You can ask click on the website www.easyjobhk.com for more details about the company

Job Descriptions:

Prepare analysis, report and presentation PowerPoint for management review and regional meeting;  
Coordinate and communicate with Supplier/factories for testing & inspection procedures;
Manage incoming 3rd party inspection reports and work with suppliers on any issues;
Manage due diligence chemical testing;
Support Head of QA in TQM development and follow up factory audit CAP filing and review;
General admin support to QA team, create, maintain and file QA records (Inspection Certificate, Seal sample records, Factory audit reports);
Manage incoming Market Product Claims;
Support QA operation and Ad hoc projects

Qualifications:


Degree in apparel design or related discipline; 
2-3 experiences of experience in fashion industry preferred (fresh graduates are also welcome); 
Good team player with sound communication skills; 
Able to multi-task and work in a fast-paced environment;
Fluent in English
Computer skills (Windows, Microsoft Office, Illustrator, etc.);
Strong in data analysis & IT skills i.e. Excel, PowerPoint

Interested parties please apply with detailed resume with current & expected salary.

Interested parties, please submit your job application and specify the product categories you have handled in your job experience.

Responsibilities:

Responsible for performing market research on the up-coming fashion trend;
Assemble and execute plans for seasonal brand assortment and OTB in order to meet the company’s business objective;
Products sourcing and sell-thru analysis;
Liaise with suppliers on order placing efficiency and ensure appropriate levels of stock of designated product categories are maintained;
Allocate merchandises and coordinate with shops and warehouse to smooth the stock replenishment issue;
Work closely with operations, visual merchandising team and other counterparts to maximize sales performance of responsible category;
Cultivate and maintain partnership relationship with suppliers

Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree holder
Min. 4 years’ apparel / footwear buying experience
Solid experience in branded merchandise buying, store replenishment, merchandise consolidation and product management is a must
Strong business sense with excellent negotiation, interpersonal, numerical and analytical skills
Fluent in spoken and written English, Chinese and Mandarin
Proficient in MS Excel (Pivot Table, VLookup and other formula functions)
Willing to travel
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Assistant Buyer

Interested parties please send your resume with current and expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".


Data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

For company information, please visit our website www.sportshouse.com.hk

Responsibilities:

Provide on site/remote support for end users;
Provide Cloud infrastructure and maintain Microsoft Azure cloud services, Office 365, SharePoint services and security setup; 
Maintain operations of company LAN, WLAN, MPLS, WAN and maintain all IT related equipment; firewall and related devices;
Maintain operation of virtual infrastructure and fine tune resources according to utilization;
Establish disaster recovery plan and procedure and carry out regular backup;
Introduce IT technologies to the company, carry out product / services; evaluation and cost comparison
Formulate IT capex and opex budget;
Supervise subordinates

Requirements:

Degree holder in Computer Science or related disciplines.
3 years or above working experience in IT technical support or related fields, candidate with less experience will be considered for the post of Technical Support Engineer.
Experiences in the following technologies are preferred:
Microsoft Azure Cloud, Microsoft AD
Network technologies: TCP/IP, MPLS, routing, switch, router, wireless, IP phone, video conference
Firewall, VPN, end points protection, digital certificates
VMWare
Disaster recovery, backup
Good command of both written and spoken in Chinese, English and Mandarin

Major roles:

Effectively lead and manage the Merchandising & Purchasing and Central Procurement teams as part of monitoring the critical path from product development to goods delivery;
Report to the Chief Commercial Officer;
Keep abreast of the market trend and carry out excellent customer relationship management to meet different markets’ and customers’ changing needs in a competitive approach;
Set sourcing strategies for relevant countries of origin, in particular China and Vietnam, in support of new and existing product development;
Devise innovative approach to achieve best pricing;
Devise best-in-class and continue to improve procurement processes, and provide direction on assessing and monitoring supplier capabilities in the areas of fabric and trims;
Support business growth strategies across customer accounts by providing insights and directions on business model based on the company’s strengths and dynamic global market situation.
Set up sales and sourcing strategies and targets for different sales regions / customers / suppliers and to strive for meeting / exceeding the related KPIs;
Station in Guangdong province for 4 days per week and in Hong Kong for 1 day per week;
Occasional overseas travelling required;

Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree holder or above in Fashion / Textiles / Clothing or related disciplines, with at least 10 years’ experience at managerial level in the apparel industry;
A mature leader, independent, pro-active, well-organised, creative, and result-oriented;
Strong business acumen, analytical, problems solving, and negotiation skills;
Knowledgeable and experienced in product development, sourcing, and production processes, preferably in the lingerie / swimwear areas, and European / North American experience & exposure, a definite asset;
Strong interpersonal and communication skills and good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficient in computer applications, such as MS Office / ERP system

We offer a competitive compensation package to the right candidate. Please apply with full resume including salary expectation and availability by clicking "Apply Now".

All data collected will only be used for recruitment purpose and kept confidential.

Merchandiser


Responsibilities:

Assist the Merchandise Manager to handle merchandising process from sample development until shipment delivery;
Familiar with development and production process;
Ability to communicate with Customers, vendors and QA independently on development or production schedule;
Perform other ad-hoc projects as assigned.

 Requirements:

Solid merchandising experiences in Garment field;
Proficiency in Excel and PowerPoint;
Independent and able to work under pressure to meet tight working schedule;
Energetic with can-do attitude;
Sufficient communication skills in English and Mandarin;
Occasional travel is required.
Less experience will be considered as Assistant Merchandiser;

Interested parties please apply with full resume, present / expected salary, and date of availability.

Job Responsibilities

Adhere to and drive 4 initiatives for GANT sourcing including: Sustainability, Quality, Speed and Transparency;
Responsible for monitoring critical path including delivery of trims and fabric to supplier for on-time delivery of salesman samples and bulk to designated customers / markets;
Provide support new supplier on boarding, development, cost analysis, price negotiation and system updates; Work with supplier on new innovative product options;
Ensure suppliers are well-adhered with GANT standard and support in new project roll out and supplier training;
Collaborate with head office and suppliers to eliminate open issues and mitigate risks of delay in both development and bulk;
Manage weekly production risk assessment and work on corrective action plan with suppliers;
Update order status and weekly schedule on delivery process;
Work with Logistics team for shipment, custom issues and delivery;
Assist in ad hoc tasks as assigned

Job Requirements

High Diploma or above in Textile or related discipline;
5+ years of relevant working experience in retail brand, preferably gained in buying office or multi-national companies;
Strong knowledge on specific product category (Home Textile);
Familiar with product development procedure and schedule;
Good system and data management;
A good team player with sound communication and interpersonal skills;
Attentive to details and good organization skills;
Good command of English and Chinese (Mandarin and Cantonese);
Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel & PowerPoint, knowledge for PLM system will be of an advantage;
Occasional travel is required

Interested parties, please submit your job application and specify the product categories you have handled in your job experience.

